latestPosts.caption:
In a world where images are often presented with perfection, the definition of beauty has been influenced by external pressures and societal standards that can sometimes feel unattainable. To break away from these constraints and celebrate the diverse expressions of beauty, fashion, and personal identity, content creator @leishapatidarrr and Social Ketchup have joined forces for this month’s magazine edition.

Our cover star, @leishapatidarrr, embodies inclusive beauty, and the cover serves as a testament to this celebration. Together, our aim is to share this celebration of beauty with you and invite you to join us on a journey of self-acceptance and embracing beauty in all its forms.

Within the pages of this edition, you’ll find a reflection of our commitment to embracing the spectrum of beauty in both online and offline realms. The stories shared by various creators inspire us to recognize beauty in its truest and most authentic manifestations.

Click on the link in bio to scroll through the magazine.

#GraziaBeauty If there is one trend that defined this year more than anything, it’s espresso make-up. Whether it was the virality of Rhode’s blush in the shade ‘Toast’ or make-up trends in coffee names, shades of brown have been all over our FYPs, so much so that the 2025 Pantone Color Of The Year was named Mocha Mousse. But it was espresso make-up that stole the spotlight. A sultrier and sexier rendition of the latte make-up, this trend is all about using deep and dark brown tones.

Words: Konika Dutta 
Photograph: Yusuf Lokhandwala
Make-up: Saikat Chakraborty, National Artist, M.A.C Cosmetics India
Hair: Shimchuila Mungkung (Ashim) and Nikesh Sharma, Looks Salon
